title: Rewind today's SEC football coaches teleconference with Ron Higgins
text:
LSU/SEC columnist Ron Higgins followed today's SEC's football coaches weekly teleconference. He posted highlights in the comments section below of what each coach said, starting with new South Carolina interim coach Shawn Elliott.
For Les Miles' comments as the teleconference's first coach to speak, check out LSU beat writer Jim Kleinpeter's separate report.
The order of coaches after Miles.:
10:10 a.m. Shawn Elliott, South Carolina
10:20 a.m. Jim McElwain, Florida
10:30 a.m. Derek Mason, Vanderbilt
10:40 a.m. Nick Saban, Alabama
10:50 a.m. Butch Jones, Tennessee
11:00 a.m. Bret Bielema, Arkansas
11:10 a.m. Gary Pinkel, Missouri
11:20 a.m. Hugh Freeze, Ole Miss
11:30 a.m. Kevin Sumlin, Texas A&M
11:40 a.m. Mark Stoops, Kentucky
11:50 a.m. Dan Mullen, Mississippi State
12:00 p.m. Mark Richt, Georgia
12:10 p.m. Gus Malzahn, Auburn
